{"questionId":"23005","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Biochemical oxygen demand (BOD) can be determined by the Winkler Method.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A 25.00 cm<sup>3</sup> sample of water was treated according to the Winkler Method.</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:60px;\">Step I:&nbsp; &nbsp;2Mn<sup>2+ </sup>(aq) + O<sub>2 </sub>(g) + 4OH<sup>− </sup>(aq) → 2MnO<sub>2 </sub>(s) + 2H<sub>2</sub>O (l)</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:60px;\">Step II:&nbsp; MnO<sub>2 </sub>(s) + 2I<sup>− </sup>(aq) + 4H<sup>+ </sup>(aq) → Mn<sup>2+ </sup>(aq) + I<sub>2 </sub>(aq) + 2H<sub>2</sub>O (l)</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:60px;\">Step III: 2S<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub><sup>2− </sup>(aq) + I<sub>2 </sub>(aq) → 2I<sup>− </sup>(aq) + S<sub>4</sub>O<sub>6</sub><sup>2− </sup>(aq)</p>\n<p>The iodine produced was titrated with 37.50 cm<sup>3</sup> of 5.000 × 10<sup>−4 </sup>mol dm<sup>−3</sup> Na<sub>2</sub>S<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the concentration of dissolved oxygen, in mol dm<sup>−3</sup>, in the sample.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>875</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math>» 4.688 × 10<sup>−6 </sup>«mol» ✔</p>\n<p>«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>688</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>mol</mi></mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>1000</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math>» 1.875 × 10<sup>−4 </sup>«mol dm<sup>−3</sup>» ✔</p>\n<p><em><br>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23005","referenceCode":"21N.2.hl.TZ0.6c(iii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the concentration of dissolved oxygen, in mol dm−3, in the sample.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(iii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.3 Reacting masses and volumes","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}